<DOC><DOCNO> AP890511-0239 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-05-11-89 0910EST</FILEID><FIRST>r f PM-Pepperell-Layoffs     05-11 0169</FIRST><SECOND>PM-Pepperell-Layoffs,0178</SECOND><HEAD>WestPoint Pepperell Fires 150 Management Employees</HEAD><DATELINE>WEST POINT, Ga. (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   West Point Pepperell Inc., asanticipated, has announced it is cutting roughly 10 percent of itshigh-level employees at the textile giant's headquarters.   The company said Wednesday 150 employees would be dismissed inan effort to speed decision-making and improve the company'scompetitiveness following its $3 billion acquisition earlier thisyear by Farley Industries Inc.   No plant workers will be affected by the restructuring,Pepperrell said.   William Farley, chairman of Chicago-based Farley Industries,said recently that cost-cutting measures at the corporateheadquarters would be coming as soon as possible.   Dismissed workers will receive a minimum three months' severancepay and company-paid medical, insurance and other workers' benefitsfor a year.   The restructuring will ``control overhead and remove layers ofbureaucracy between decisions and decision-makers, and allow us tomove faster in a fast-moving world,'' the company's statement said.   ``WestPoint Pepperell will be stronger, leaner and more able todeal with international competition,'' the statement said.</TEXT></DOC>